%N A255248 Fundamental positive solution y = y2(n) of the second class of the Pell equation x^2 - 2*y^2 = -A001132(n), n>=1 (primes congruent to {1,7} mod 8).
%C A255248 For the corresponding term x2(n) see A255247(n).
%C A255248 See the comments on A255247.
%F A255248 A255247(n)^2 - 2*a(n)^2 = -A001132(n), n >= 1, gives the second smallest positive (proper) solution of this (generalized) Pell equation.
%F A255248 a(n) = -(2*A255235(n+1) - 3*A255246(n+1)), n >= 1.
%e A255248 See A255247.
%e A255248 a(4) = -(2*1 - 3*4) = 12 - 2 = 10.
%e A255248 n=4: 13^2 - 2*10^2 = 169 - 200 = -31 = -A001132(4).
